Cell.Text: Alduin... we heard the Dragonrend Shout from here... you defeated him?
[S] <<Shared>> The old tales say that he is able to travel into Sovngarde to devour the souls of the dead. | But they don't say how he does this.
Yes, but he escaped. I need to find his portal to Sovngarde.
[S] I feared as much. I thought it was him we saw flying east after your battle.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirIntroA1: Yes, but he escaped. I need to find out where he went.

Cell.Text: Yes, of course! But how to force a dragon to talk to you... | There is one possibility. But... no, the Jarl would never agree.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirFindAlduinA1: One of his dragon allies could tell us...

Cell.Text: Do you know Dragonsreach? The Jarl of Whiterun's palace? | Its name is no accident. The palace was originally built to hold a captive dragon.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeiFindAlduinB1: The Jarl? What are you talking about?

Cell.Text: Oh, this was back in the days of Olaf One-Eye, thousands of years ago. | In those days, dragons could still be found among the remote mountain peaks. | Before the Blades wiped them all out.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirFindAlduinC1: But I thought there weren't any dragons until Alduin came back.

Cell.Text: [S] You might be able to trap him there, exactly. | You'd require the Jarl's cooperation, of course. That might not be easy to come by. | You must trust in the rightness of your cause, and the strength of your Voice.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirFindAlduinC2: So if I could lure a dragon into Dragonsreach...

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> The old tales say that he is able to travel into Sovngarde to devour the souls of the dead. | But they don't say how he does this.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirFindAlduinTopic: I need to find where Alduin fled to.

Cell.Text: [S] We are not warriors. What is overlooked in the Dragonborn is not permitted to any other followers of the Way of the Voice.
I'm going to try to capture a dragon, if will help me.

[S] Ah! Dragonsreach! There are many difficulties, but I cannot think of a better plan. | Although I fear the Jarl may not be easy to persuade. | Remember, the Way of the Voice trains you for more than battle. Indeed, we believe that battle is the least of its uses. | May the strength and truth of your Voice serve you well. Breath and focus.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirIntroB1: I need your help. I need to capture a dragon.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You misunderstand our authority. The Greybeards have never involved themselves in political affairs.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirIntroC1: I'll worry about capturing a dragon. I need your help to stop the war.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You misunderstand our authority. The Greybeards have never involved themselves in political affairs.
Are you ready to host the peace council?
Deliver the message to the warring parties. If they will listen, I will do what I can to bring them to terms.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirPeaceConferenceTopic: I need your help to stop the war.

Cell.Text: I see. The dragon will lead you to Alduin, but without the Jarl's help...

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirPeaceConferenceA1: Jarl won't help me while the war rages.

Cell.Text: [S] Paarthurnax has made the decision to help you. This is the road we have to walk. | Even the Greybeards must bend to the winds of change, it seems. | So be it. Tell Ulfric and General Tullius that the Greybeards wish to speak to them. | We will see if they still remember us.

Node.Caption: MQ301ArngeirPeaceConferenceB1: Both sides respect the Greybeards. They will listen.
